HANTAVIRUS UPDATE 2012 - AMERICAS (01): CHILE
*********************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this update, cases in Chile:
[1] Lago Conguillio area, Araucania region
[2] Lago Conguillio area and Icalma, Lonquimay, Malleco area,
Araucania region
[3] Mulchen, Bio-Bio region

******
[1] Lago Conguillio area, Araucania region
Date: Sat 31 Dec 2011
Source: Diario Las Noticias de Victoria [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY,
edited]
http://lasnoticiasdevictoria.cl/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=8345


Yesterday [30 Dec 2011] at 23:30 hrs, a 27-year old male patient was
admitted to the intensive care unit of the Victoria Hospital with
severe respiratory complications. He was brought from the Curacautin
Hospital. The rapid test for [a] hantavirus [infection] was positive,
and he was diagnosed with a serious clinical picture and hepatic,
respiratory, and renal insufficiency. Today in the morning
(yesterday), he was sent to the ICU of Hospital Guillermo Grant
Benavente in the city of Concepcion.

Information provided by the family stated that the patient had been in
an area near Lake Conguillio.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Andes virus transmission summer season has begun in Chile again
this year. The timeline of the movement of this patient is not exactly
clear. However, from the report below, this patient died on the way to
the Hospital Guillermo Grant Benavente.

Although not stated, the hantavirus involved in this and the cases
below is Andes virus.

An image of the long-tailed pygmy rice rat (_Oligoryzomys
longicaudatus_), the sigmodontine rodent host of Andes hantavirus, can
be seen at http://www.bios.niu.edu/frayjorge/rod6.jpg.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of beautiful Lago
Conguillio in the Araucania region can be accessed at
http://healthmap.org/r/1BII. - Mod.TY]

******
[2] Lago Conguillio area and Icalma, Lonquimay, Malleco area,
Araucania region
Date: Tue 3 Jan 2012
Source: Diario Las Noticias de Victoria [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY,
edited]
http://lasnoticiasdevictoria.cl/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=8391


The director of the Victoria Hospital, Joaquin Sanzana Munoz,
yesterday [2 Jan 2012] confirmed to Las Noticias in Malleco the deaths
of 2 people, victims of [a] hantavirus [infection].

The director said that the 1st case, reported promptly to this
newspaper, relates to a young 27-year-old man, resident of Curacautin
who had come form the Lago Conguillio area; he received initial
medical attention in the assistance center and later, due to his
serious condition, was sent to the ICU of the Hospital "Guillermo
Grant Benavente" in Concepcion, and died en route.

The 2nd [case] corresponds to a 50-year-old person, native of Icalma,
who was admitted to the Victoria Hospital at noon of Saturday, 31 Dec
[2011], and died on 1 Jan [2012], victim of the virus.

Dr Sanzana said that given the summer conditions, it is recommended
that those who visit places or houses that are little used, make sure
that these habitations are aired out. This is the way to avoid
infection, said the physician, noting also that when installing tents
in recreational areas, to clean up the environment. "Rat feces
[contaminated with a virus] that is inhaled causes the disease
[transmits the virus], [with initial symptoms] similar to a cold, so
it is recommended that [an ill individual] go to a medical
professional, when there is a suspicion [of a hantavirus infection]."

[Byline: Guillermo Herrera]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap alerts
