[The 1st case mentioned is the same one in the report above.
Unfortunately, the man died while being transported to the ICU of the
Hospital Guillermo Grant Benavente in the city of Concepcion.

A map showing the location of Icalma, Lonquimay, Malleco area in the
Araucania region can be accessed at
http://www.maplandia.com/chile/malleco/lonquimay/icalma/. - Mod.TY]

******
[3] Mulchen, Bio-Bio region
Date: Tue 3 Jan 2012
Source: Radio Bio-Bio [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2012/01/03/joven-afectado-por-virus-hanta-permanece-grave-en-hospital-de-los-angeles.shtml


A 24 year-old young man from the Mulchen commune [smallest
administrative subdivision in Chile] was admitted into the intensive
care unit of the Hospital Base de Los Angeles, where he remains in
serious condition due to [a] hantavirus [infection]. The patient is
stable although in serious condition, and is connected to a mechanical
ventilator.

The health authority is working to establish the place where the virus
infection took place, and is carrying out related tests on the rest of
his family group. [Andes virus is the only hantavirus know to be
transmitted directly from person to person, although this transmission
requires close physical contact, usually between family members.
Hence, the followup with family members in this case. - Mod.TY]

[Byline: Erasmo Tauran; information from Sergio Osses]

